      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEA POEM (4) looks nicely placed to peak third up. Two runs back have been encouraging, getting into the minor placings each time and only beaten a long neck at Sandown Lakeside second up. 1400m from a soft draw looks ideal and she should go close. TEMPRANILLO (6) caught the eye with a big run from a tough spot first up in the same race. She'll be fitter now and harder to hold out up in trip. SILENT SHARES (1) can mix her form a bit but did grab third in the Leilani Final at Flemington last time which is very good form for this. Up in the weights but gets a handy claim and is well placed. SECOND TIME (7) is a lightly raced mare who has won 2/3 in her maiden campaign, dominant on the synthetic latest. Can measure up again.",
